item.description:
The Reserve Bank of India is working on a plan to reduce online transaction costs as it tries to encourage more digital banking, two parliamentary panel members quoted central bank governor Urjit Patel as saying on Friday.
&ldquo;We are working on a mechanism to bring down transaction costs,&rdquo; one member of the public accounts committee quoted Mr Patel as saying. &ldquo;We are speaking to all stakeholders.&rdquo;
Mr Patel met the panel to answer questions about the November 8 abolition of Rs 500 and Rs 1,000 notes, or 86 per cent of the currency then in circulation.
